            <div n="1"> <head>COLONIAL SOCIETY.</head> <lb break="yes"/> 
                <p>The following communication was resolved upon at a spe-<lb break="no"/>cial meeting of the Colonial Society, convened to congratu-<lb break="no"/>late that distinguished philosopher, the Baron de Humboldt,<lb break="yes"/>upon his arrival in England, and to elect him an honorary<lb break="yes"/>member of the society:&#x2014;</p> <lb break="yes"/> <floatingText> <body> <opener> <dateline> <hi rendition="#et">&#x201C;Colonial Society, Jan. 29, 1842.</hi> </dateline> </opener> <lb break="yes"/> <p>&#x201C;Sir&#x2014;The committee of the Colonial Society, in con-<lb break="no"/>formity with a resolution unanimously adopted this day, beg<lb break="yes"/>leave to express their gratification at your visit to this coun-<lb break="no"/>try, in the suite of your distinguished Sovereign.</p> <lb break="yes"/> <p>&#x201C;Identified as the Colonial Society is with the extension<lb break="yes"/>of civilisation, and the development of the internal re-<lb break="no"/>sources of distant and imperfectly known foreign regions,<lb break="yes"/>the society gladly avails itself of the present opportunity to<lb break="yes"/>tender its respectful congratulations to a philosopher, whose<lb break="yes"/>invaluable services in the cause of geographical discovery<lb break="yes"/>and humanity are acknowledged and justly appreciated by<lb break="yes"/>all civilised nations, for they have had for their special ob-<lb break="no" />ject the welfare and advancement of mankind.</p> <lb break="yes"/> <p>&#x201C;Understanding that your sojourn in England is neces-<lb break="no"/>sarily brief, the society is obliged to refrain from tendering<lb break="yes"/>at present any other mark of their sincere esteem, than that<lb break="yes"/>of naming you an honorary member of their body, and in<lb break="yes"/>doing so they would beg to offer their heartfelt wishes for<lb break="yes"/>your continued health and happiness.</p> <closer>&#x2014;By order of the com-<lb break="no"/>mittee, <hi rendition="#et">&#x201C;<hi rendition="#k">Julius Le Souef,</hi> Sec.</hi> <lb break="yes"/>&#x201C;The Baron de Humboldt, &#x0026;c.&#x201D;</closer> </body> </floatingText> <lb break="yes"/> <milestone unit="section" rendition="#hr"/> <lb break="yes"/> <p>Baron von Humboldt returned the following answer: &#x2014;</p> <floatingText> <body> <opener> <dateline>&#x201C;Windsor Castle, <choice><sic>ce</sic><corr type="editorial">le</corr></choice> 30 Janvr. 1842.</dateline> </opener> <lb break="yes"/> <p>&#x201C;Monsieur,&#x2014;Dans la vie <choice><sic>agiteé</sic><corr type="editorial">agitée</corr></choice> que nous ménons pendant<lb break="yes"/>le trop court séjour de mon Souverain en Angleterre, il ne<lb break="yes"/>me reste que le regret de ne pas avoir un moment de libre pour<lb break="yes"/>exprimer personellement au Comité de l&#x2019;illustre &#x201C;<hi rendition="#i">Colonial<lb break="yes"/>Society</hi>&#x201D; la vive reconnaissance dont je me sens pénétré.<lb break="yes"/>Je vous supplie, Monsieur, de vouloir bien &#x00EA;tre l&#x2019;interpréte<lb break="yes"/>de mes sentimens respectueux. Rien ne pourrait &#x00EA;tre plus<lb break="yes"/>flatteur pour moi que l&#x2019;intér&#x00EA;t que mes faibles efforts ont<lb break="yes"/>pu inspirer à une réunion dont les travaux tendent à un<lb break="yes"/><choice><sic>qut</sic><corr type="editorial">but</corr></choice> si noble et si bienfaisant pour l&#x2019;humanité.</p> <lb break="yes"/> <closer> <salute>&#x201C;Agréez, <choice><sic>Moesieur</sic><corr type="editorial">Monsieur</corr></choice>, je vous supplie, l&#x2019;homage de la haute<lb break="yes"/>considération avec laquelle j&#x2019;ai l&#x2019;honneur d&#x2019;&#x00EA;tre,&#x2014;Mon-<lb break="no" />sieur, votre très humble et très obéissant serviteur,</salute> <lb break="yes"/> <hi rendition="#et">&#x201C;<hi rendition="#k">Le Bn. de Humboldt.</hi> </hi> <lb break="yes"/>&#x201C;Monsr. Julius Le Souef, &#x0026;c.&#x201D;</closer> 
                </body> </floatingText> </div> <lb break="yes"/> 
